<br>
First, the Thrar and Co. way (or the small single group method):  Party commie loots and the cost of spell components is ripped off of the top before split.  This is the best way to handle a small group of characters run by friends.<br>
<br>
Second, the Pickup Raid method:  All persons joining raid are required to &quot;buy&quot; in with the appropriate stones which are collected by the raid leader and distributed to the casters.  This is the best method if you aren't sure who's coming and if you don't want to levy some dues system on the guild.  The draw back here is that there can be NO exceptions.  You are relying on the raid members to provide materials needed for the raid, showing up with 120PP instead of 10 peridots won't cut it.  Showing up empty handed won't cut it either.<br>
<br>
Third, the casters loot gems method:  all gem drops are scooped up by the casters, commie pooled and split at the end of the night to cover costs.  This works great in some areas and not so great in others.  Frequently used in Hate where gem drops are common.<br>
<br>
Fourth, the euber system:  Guild fronts cost of all gems.  This cost requires and extensive guild treasury which is funded by either guild dues or selling euber loot in GBay. <p><B><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=2>Forin Ironshield</B><BR>
